cavity may furnish the in-
dividuals which have been found
at Adelsberg & at Sittich. -
[underline]Eubathes[/underline] - This is a very ex-
traordinary view of the Subject:
is it not possible that it may
be the larva of some large
unknown Animal inhabiting
these limestone cavities - Its
feet are not in harmony
with the rest of it's organization
& were they removed it would
have all the characters of a
fish. -
[person]person_122|[underline]The Unknown[/underline][/person] - I cannot suppose
