this body is rendered happy
or miserable for actions
committed by another & an
extinct frame. A particular
organisation of the [deletion]frames[/deletion]
stomach or several organs
leads to improper & immoral
gratification; it does not
appear to me ascending to
the principles of eternal
justice that the body of the
resurrection should be
punished for crimes de-
pendant upon a conformation
now dissolved & destroyed. -
[person]person_122|[underline]The Unknown[/underline][/person]. Nothing is
more absurd, I may say
more uniform than for man
with a ken surrounded by
the dense mists of sense,
to [underline]reason[/underline] respecting the
decrees of eternal justice.

[page]96|MS-DAVY-11401-000-00096|dnp14a096pp|92018156[/page]
you adopt here the same
limited view that you
embraced in reasoning
against the indestructibility
of the sentient principle
in man , from the apparent
[insertion]division[/insertion] of the living principle in
the polypus, not recollecting
that to [deletion]im[/deletion]prove a quality
can be increased or
exalted does not prove
that it can be annihilated.
If there be, which I think
cannot be doubted, a
consciousness of good & evil
constantly belonging to
the sentient principle in
man, the rewards & punish
ments naturally belong to
the acts of this consciousness
- to obedience or disobedience;
& the indestructibility of the

[page]97|MS-DAVY-11401-000-00097|dnp14a097pp|92018157[/page]
97
sentient being is necessary to
the decrees of eternal justice
on your view even in [underline]this[/underline]
[underline]life[/underline], [underline]just[/underline] punishments for
crimes would be almost
impossible, for the materials
of which human beings are
composed change rapidly
& in a few years probably
not an atom of the primitive
structure remains, yet even
the materialist is obliged in
old age to do penance for
the sins of his youth, &
does not complain of the
injustice of his decrepit
body entirely changed &
made stiff by time,- suffering
for the intemperance of his
vigorous youthful & flexible
organs. On my idea conscience
is the frame of the mind
fitted for it's probation in

[page]98|MS-DAVY-11401-000-00098|dnp14a098pp|92018158[/page]
